❤ Loved by Japanese for over 50 years❤

Calbee prawn crackers were first made in january 1964.

The Japanese fell in love with the high nutritional value
and flavor of Calbee prawn crackers, which are so good
that you just can't put them down.





Prawn Crackers
かっぱえびせん


Calbee prawn crackers, which recreate the delicious flavor of prawn tempura, are the favorite Japanese snack of today.






Main Ingredients

  • Wheat
  • Flour
  • Palm Oil
  • Fresh Prawn

For allergen advise see ingredients highlighted in BOLD.

Produced in a factory where milk, fish, crustacean, shellfish, tree nut (coconut), peanuts and sesame products are also handled.
